other_tests.findings: Multiple loculated rim enhancing fluid collections with extensive fat stranding centered about a tubular appearing dilated fluid-filled structure likely reflecting an inflamed appendix which has ruptured, with phlegmonous changes and multiple loculated fluid collections measuring approximately 7.2 x 3.3 x 5.9 cm. The report indicates appendiceal wall dehiscence near the base and tip, and extensive edematous and hyperemia of the terminal ileum and cecum.
